text: I always feel a profound sadness when I listen to rain sounds or whale song, because being aware at the noise's being artificial is truly unbearable, but you can take solace in remembering it was recorded in a real rainstorm and a real whale with a liver and a heart once sang it.

Always better to open a window and listen to the cars outside. Reality is always better than any fantasy. If one pretends his house is a castle, the castle is always inferior to the real house. If we are unable to see it, it is because of our atrophied sight. Ban rain sounds now.

I get delusional looking at my refrigerator full of sausages, smoked fish, ice cream, etc. and start thinking I'm eating like a king. Especially the dairy stuff like cheese and yogurt just fascinates me like I'm a Medieval peasant. If you ever feel sad overfill your refrigerator.

Lots of folks here who want to raise backyard chickens Danny Roddy style one day, but I think pigeons are another fun idea. One guy has a few dozen in a pigeon coop on his garage roof, just next to the street. Takes very little space, they seem to do very ok even in urban areas.
In my neighborhood that is, I pass by them on my daily walks. I'd assume quails are another good choice. Or ostriches. Think bigger.

It's important to keep a few bottles of beer in your refrigerator even if you're not a massive beer drinker imo. Just brings the refrigerator aesthetic together. Once in a blue moon, when you feel like drinking some beer, it will be there waiting for you. Also some instant ramen.
I like it on baked potatoes

Fruit Ninja, Flappy Bird, Angry Birds, etc. are a very fun memory from a brief 2013 era when smartphones were new and everyone was excited at exploring the possibilities they offered before realizing literally nothing can be compared to social media in terms of pure pleasure.

Those 3D VR glasses are the same type of vaporwave (which is why the Apple product is literally advertised with "Fruit Ninja"). What can we use this new exciting technologoy for? Accessing social media and posting on twitter. Which is done best with a keyboard or a smartphone.
There is no better pleasure than conversation, discoursing, talking, exchanging letters, etc.

I need to figure out a better scheme for getting more people to convert to Orthodox Christianity, but for now all I can come up with is just replying " you should become Orthodox" to people when the topic comes up. Just doesn't have that power of persuasion I've been looking for.

It's uhh the original church. Christianity 1.0, literally unchanged since day one. No additions. Just us doing the same stuff for like 2000+ years now. Lots of miracles occur on a daily basis. There are other arguments too, but I'm still working on framing them in a catchier way.
I guess you gotta study the icon idea and the symbolism and stuff. It's not that different from prayers, it's basically writing more than painting
